"title": "5186: stumbling",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5186: stumbling",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Faltering or falling in the course of running or walking. The term is also used metaphorically to refer to failure, hesitation or difficulty.</p>\n<h2>Physical stumbling</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:14\">LEV 19:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:37\">LEV 26:37</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:4\">ISA 21:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:7\">ISA 28:7</a> <em>through drunkenness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:5\">NAM 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:3\">NAM 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>God protects his people from stumbling</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps56:13\">PSA 56:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:4\">1SA 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job4:4\">JOB 4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:24\">PSA 37:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:8\">PSA 116:8</a></p>\n<h2>The enemies of God's people will stumble</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:11\">JER 20:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps9:3\">PSA 9:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps27:2\">PSA 27:2</a></p>\n<h2>God's people will stumble if they sin</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa8:14\">ISA 8:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:16\">JER 13:16</a></p>\n<h2>Avoiding stumbling by keeping God's law</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:165\">PSA 119:165</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:23\">PRO 3:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:26\">PRO 3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:11-Prov4:12\">PRO 4:11–4:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:7-Isa26:8\">ISA 26:7–26:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:30-Isa40:31\">ISA 40:30–40:31</a></p>\n<h2>The wicked stumble because they reject God's way</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:19\">PRO 4:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos14:9\">HOS 14:9</a></p>\n<h2>Causes of stumbling</h2>\n<h3>Dishonesty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:14\">ISA 59:14</a></p>\n<h3>Arrogance</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:32\">JER 50:32</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos5:5\">HOS 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>False teaching by religious leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:5\">HOS 4:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:8\">MAL 2:8</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:15\">JER 18:15</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in riches</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek7:19\">EZK 7:19</a></p>\n<h3>Trust in secular political alliances</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:3\">ISA 31:3</a></p>\n<h2>Stumbling as a consequence of sin and divine judgment</h2>\n<h3>Making one's own stumbling-block</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:3-Ezek14:4\">EZK 14:3–14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:7\">EZK 14:7</a></p>\n<h3>Stumbling over obstacles sent by God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:21\">JER 6:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:16\">JER 13:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:20\">EZK 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Some stumbling is educative or disciplinary</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:35\">DAN 11:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:32-Rom9:33\">ROM 9:32–9:33</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as the light that prevents believers from stumbling</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:5\">JHN 9:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:9-John11:10\">JHN 11:9–11:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ as a stumbling-block for unbelievers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:23\">1CO 1:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:8\">1PE 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>Stumbling and sin</h2>\n<h3>All sin and stumble</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:10\">JAS 2:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:2\">JAS 3:2</a></p>\n<h3>None should feel superior to others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:17\">PRO 24:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:12\">1CO 10:12</a></p>\n<h3>None should cause others to stumble</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:20\">ROM 14:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:32\">1CO 10:32</a></p>",
